        </div>

        <!-- Signature card -->
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden" style="background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-3.5"
               style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full" style="background: #6ee7b7;"></div>
              <span class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider" style="color: var(--fg);">Signature</span>
            </div>
            <button data-copy="signature"
              class="text-xs font-medium px-2.5 py-1 rounded-lg transition-all"
              style="background: var(--accent-muted); color: var(--accent); border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.2);"
              onmouseover="this.style.background='rgba(99,102,241,0.18)'"
              onmouseout="this.style.background='var(--accent-muted)'">Copy</button>
          </div>
          <div class="mx-5 mt-4 mb-3 px-3 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-xs leading-relaxed"
               style="background: rgba(234,179,8,0.07); border: 1px solid rgba(234,179,8,0.18); color: var(--fg2);">
            <span style="color: #ca8a04; font-weight: 600;">Note:</span> Signature verification requires the secret key and is not performed by this tool. The value shown is the raw signature string from the token.
          </div>
          <pre id="signatureOutput" class="px-5 pb-5 pt-2 text-xs overflow-auto"
               style="font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace; color: var(--fg2); background: transparent; margin: 0; white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-all;"></pre>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

  </section>

  <!-- ── FAQ ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="pb-16 max-w-3xl mx-auto reveal">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-8 text-center" style="color: var(--fg);">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-2">

      <div class="faq-item rounded-xl overflow-hidden" style="border: 1px solid var(--border);">
        <button class="faq-q w-full flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-5 py-4 text-left text-sm font-medium"
                style="background: var(--card); color: var(--fg);">
          What is a JWT decoder?
          <svg class="faq-chevron w-4 h-4 shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a hidden px-5 pb-5 pt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed" style="background: var(--card); color: var(--fg2);">
          A JWT decoder is a tool that reads a JSON Web Token and displays its contents in plain readable JSON. A JWT has three parts separated by dots: the header, the payload, and the signature. The header describes the algorithm used to sign the token. The payload contains the actual claims like user ID, expiry time, and issuer. Decoding simply means reading these parts, which are Base64 encoded, not encrypted.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item rounded-xl overflow-hidden" style="border: 1px solid var(--border);">
        <button class="faq-q w-full flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-5 py-4 text-left text-sm font-medium"
                style="background: var(--card); color: var(--fg);">
          Can I decode a JWT without a secret key?
          <svg class="faq-chevron w-4 h-4 shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a hidden px-5 pb-5 pt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed" style="background: var(--card); color: var(--fg2);">
          Yes. Decoding a JWT does not require a secret key because the token is encoded not encrypted. Anyone with the token can read the header and payload by Base64 decoding them. The secret key is only needed to verify the signature, which proves the token was issued by a trusted source and has not been tampered with. This tool decodes but does not verify.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item rounded-xl overflow-hidden" style="border: 1px solid var(--border);">
        <button class="faq-q w-full flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-5 py-4 text-left text-sm font-medium"
                style="background: var(--card); color: var(--fg);">
          What information can I see after decoding a JWT?
          <svg class="faq-chevron w-4 h-4 shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a hidden px-5 pb-5 pt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed" style="background: var(--card); color: var(--fg2);">
          After decoding you can see everything in the header and payload. The header typically shows the token type and signing algorithm such as HS256 or RS256. The payload shows claims like sub which is the subject or user identifier, iss which is the issuer, exp which is the expiry timestamp, and iat which is the time the token was issued. Applications can also add custom claims for their own purposes.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item rounded-xl overflow-hidden" style="border: 1px solid var(--border);">
        <button class="faq-q w-full flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-5 py-4 text-left text-sm font-medium"
                style="background: var(--card); color: var(--fg);">
          Is it safe to decode JWT tokens online?
          <svg class="faq-chevron w-4 h-4 shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a hidden px-5 pb-5 pt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed" style="background: var(--card); color: var(--fg2);">
          It is safe when the tool runs entirely in your browser without sending data to a server. This tool processes everything locally using JavaScript. Your token never leaves your machine. That said avoid pasting tokens that are still active and grant access to sensitive production systems in any public tool as a general security practice.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item rounded-xl overflow-hidden" style="border: 1px solid var(--border);">
        <button class="faq-q w-full flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-5 py-4 text-left text-sm font-medium"
                style="background: var(--card); color: var(--fg);">
          How do I decode a JWT in JavaScript?
          <svg class="faq-chevron w-4 h-4 shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a hidden px-5 pb-5 pt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed" style="background: var(--card); color: var(--fg2);">
          You can decode a JWT in JavaScript by splitting the token on the dot character, taking the second part which is the payload, and passing it to atob() to Base64 decode it, then parsing the result with JSON.parse(). For production use the jsonwebtoken library on Node.js handles both decoding and verification and is the industry standard.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item rounded-xl overflow-hidden" style="border: 1px solid var(--border);">
        <button class="faq-q w-full flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-5 py-4 text-left text-sm font-medium"
                style="background: var(--card); color: var(--fg);">
          What are the three parts of a JWT?
          <svg class="faq-chevron w-4 h-4 shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a hidden px-5 pb-5 pt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed" style="background: var(--card); color: var(--fg2);">
          A JWT consists of three Base64 encoded sections separated by dots. The first is the header which contains the token type and algorithm. The second is the payload which contains the claims or data. The third is the signature which is created by signing the header and payload with a secret key. The signature cannot be decoded, only verified using the original key.
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── SEO CONTENT ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="pb-20">
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

      <div class="reveal rounded-2xl p-6" style="background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold mb-3" style="color: var(--fg);">What is a JWT Token?</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          A JWT or JSON Web Token is a compact string made up of three parts joined by dots. The header describes the signing algorithm. The payload holds the claims, which is the actual data being transmitted. The third part is the signature, which a server uses to confirm the token has not been altered. Both the header and payload are Base64 encoded, which means anyone can read them with a jwt decoder without needing a key. Decoding is always possible but verifying the signature requires the original secret. JWTs are the standard mechanism for stateless authentication in REST APIs and web applications because they carry all the information a server needs without a database lookup.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal rounded-2xl p-6" style="background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold mb-3" style="color: var(--fg);">How JWT Authentication Works</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          When a user logs in, the server verifies their credentials and issues a signed JWT. The client stores this token, usually in memory or local storage, and sends it with every subsequent request in the Authorization header as a Bearer token. Because the server does not need to query session state from a database, this pattern is called stateless authentication. Any server that knows the signing key can validate requests independently, which makes JWT a natural fit for microservices where requests may be handled by different instances on each call. The tradeoff is that tokens cannot be invalidated server side before they expire, which is why short expiry times matter.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal rounded-2xl p-6" style="background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold mb-3" style="color: var(--fg);">Understanding JWT Claims</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          Claims are the key-value pairs stored in the JWT payload. The specification defines a set of registered claims: sub identifies the subject, which is usually a user ID; iss names the issuer of the token; exp sets the expiry timestamp; iat records when the token was issued; and nbf sets the earliest time the token becomes valid. Public claims are shared in the IANA registry to avoid naming collisions across different systems. Private claims are custom fields agreed on between the parties. Real world examples include Kubernetes service account tokens, which use sub for pod identity, and OAuth2 access tokens, which commonly carry scope and aud claims to restrict what the token can access.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal rounded-2xl p-6" style="background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold mb-3" style="color: var(--fg);">JWT Security Best Practices</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          Always verify the JWT signature server side before trusting any claim in the payload. Never rely on the payload contents alone. Use short expiry times so that stolen tokens become useless quickly. Keep in mind that the payload is only Base64 encoded and not encrypted, so anyone holding the token can read its contents. Never store passwords, credit card numbers, or other sensitive data in the payload. Always serve your application over HTTPS to prevent tokens being intercepted in transit. Rotate your signing keys on a regular schedule and revoke active tokens immediately when a breach is suspected.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="reveal mt-6 rounded-2xl p-6" style="background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--fg2);">
        If you work with JSON data try our <a href="/json-yaml-converter" style="color: var(--accent); text-decoration: underline;">JSON to YAML converter</a> to move configs between formats instantly. Need to set file permissions on your server? Use our <a href="/chmod-calculator" style="color: var(--accent); text-decoration: underline;">chmod calculator</a> to calculate the right octal value for any permission set.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</div>
</div>

</Layout>

<style>
  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    #outputGrid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
(function () {

  // ── Helpers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  function b64urlDecode(str) {
    str = str.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/');
    var pad = str.length % 4;
    if (pad === 2) str += '==';
    else if (pad === 3) str += '=';
    try {
      return decodeURIComponent(
        atob(str).split('').map(function (c) {
          return '%' + ('00' + c.charCodeAt(0).toString(16)).slice(-2);
        }).join('')
      );
    } catch (e) { return null; }
  }

  function formatDate(ts) {
    return new Date(ts * 1000).toUTCString();
  }

  function relativeTime(ts) {
    var nowSec = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);
    var diff = ts - nowSec;
    var abs = Math.abs(diff);
    var future = diff > 0;
    var str;
    if (abs < 60) { str = abs + ' second' + (abs === 1 ? '' : 's'); }
    else if (abs < 3600) { var m = Math.floor(abs / 60); str = m + ' minute' + (m === 1 ? '' : 's'); }
    else if (abs < 86400) { var h = Math.floor(abs / 3600); str = h + ' hour' + (h === 1 ? '' : 's'); }
    else { var d = Math.floor(abs / 86400); str = d + ' day' + (d === 1 ? '' : 's'); }
    return future ? 'in ' + str : str + ' ago';
  }

  function escHtml(s) {
    return String(s)
      .replace(/&/g, '&amp;').replace(/</g, '&lt;')
      .replace(/>/g, '&gt;').replace(/"/g, '&quot;');
  }

  // ── Sample JWT (assembled at runtime so claims are readable) ─────────────
  var SAMPLE_JWT = (function () {
    var hdr = '{"alg":"HS256","typ":"JWT"}';
    var pld = '{"sub":"user_42a8b93f","iss":"https://auth.example.com","aud":"api.example.com","iat":1704067200,"exp":1812499200,"nbf":1704067200,"email":"jane.doe@example.com","name":"Jane Doe","roles":["user","admin"]}';
    function enc(s) {
      return btoa(unescape(encodeURIComponent(s)))
        .replace(/\+/g, '-').replace(/\//g, '_').replace(/=+$/, '');
    }
    return enc(hdr) + '.' + enc(pld) + '.SflKxwRJSMeKKF2QT4fwpMeJf36POk6yJV_adQssw5c';
  })();

  // ── DOM refs ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  var jwtInput        = document.getElementById('jwtInput');
  var errorMsg        = document.getElementById('errorMsg');
  var statusRow       = document.getElementById('statusRow');
  var statusBanner    = document.getElementById('statusBanner');
  var algBadge        = document.getElementById('algBadge');
  var outputSection   = document.getElementById('outputSection');
  var headerOutput    = document.getElementById('headerOutput');
  var payloadOutput   = document.getElementById('payloadOutput');
  var signatureOutput = document.getElementById('signatureOutput');
  var specialClaims   = document.getElementById('specialClaims');
  var claimsDivider   = document.getElementById('claimsDivider');

  // ── Decode ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  function decode() {
    var token = jwtInput.value.trim();

    if (!token) {
      errorMsg.classList.add('hidden');
      outputSection.classList.add('hidden');
      statusRow.classList.add('hidden');
      return;
    }

    var parts = token.split('.');
    if (parts.length !== 3) {
      showError('Not a valid JWT. A JWT must have exactly three parts separated by dots.');
      return;
    }

    var headerStr  = b64urlDecode(parts[0]);
    var payloadStr = b64urlDecode(parts[1]);

    if (!headerStr) { showError('Could not decode the header section. The token may be malformed.'); return; }
    if (!payloadStr) { showError('Could not decode the payload section. The token may be malformed.'); return; }

    var header, payload;
    try { header = JSON.parse(headerStr); } catch (e) { showError('Header section is not valid JSON after decoding.'); return; }
    try { payload = JSON.parse(payloadStr); } catch (e) { showError('Payload section is not valid JSON after decoding.'); return; }

    errorMsg.classList.add('hidden');
    outputSection.classList.remove('hidden');

    // Algorithm badge
    algBadge.textContent = 'Algorithm: ' + (header.alg || 'Unknown');

    // Status banner
    renderStatusBanner(payload);
    statusRow.classList.remove('hidden');

    // Outputs
    headerOutput.textContent    = JSON.stringify(header, null, 2);
    renderSpecialClaims(payload);
    payloadOutput.textContent   = JSON.stringify(payload, null, 2);
    signatureOutput.textContent = parts[2];
  }

  function showError(msg) {
    errorMsg.textContent = msg;
    errorMsg.classList.remove('hidden');
    outputSection.classList.add('hidden');
    statusRow.classList.add('hidden');
  }

  // ── Status banner ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  function renderStatusBanner(payload) {
    if (payload.exp === undefined) {
      statusBanner.innerHTML = '<span style="font-weight:600;">No expiry claim</span><span style="opacity:0.6;font-size:0.78em;margin-left:8px;">This token has no exp field</span>';
      statusBanner.style.cssText = 'display:flex;align-items:center;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:4px;padding:10px 16px;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(107,114,128,0.25);background:rgba(107,114,128,0.08);font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--fg2);';
      return;
    }

    var expired = Date.now() > payload.exp * 1000;
    var dateStr = formatDate(payload.exp);
    var relStr  = relativeTime(payload.exp);

    if (expired) {
      statusBanner.innerHTML =
        '<span style="color:#ef4444;font-weight:700;">&#x2715; Expired</span>' +
        '<span style="opacity:0.65;font-size:0.78em;margin-left:8px;">' + escHtml(relStr) + ' &middot; ' + escHtml(dateStr) + '</span>';
      statusBanner.style.cssText = 'display:flex;align-items:center;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:4px;padding:10px 16px;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(239,68,68,0.3);background:rgba(239,68,68,0.07);font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--fg);';
    } else {
      statusBanner.innerHTML =
        '<span style="color:var(--accent);font-weight:700;">&#x2713; Valid Token</span>' +
        '<span style="opacity:0.65;font-size:0.78em;margin-left:8px;">Expires ' + escHtml(relStr) + ' &middot; ' + escHtml(dateStr) + '</span>';
      statusBanner.style.cssText = 'display:flex;align-items:center;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:4px;padding:10px 16px;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.3);background:rgba(99,102,241,0.07);font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--fg);';
    }
  }

  // ── Special claims ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  function renderSpecialClaims(payload) {
    var DEFS = [
      { key: 'sub', label: 'Subject' },
      { key: 'iss', label: 'Issuer' },
      { key: 'exp', label: 'Expires' },
      { key: 'iat', label: 'Issued At' },
      { key: 'nbf', label: 'Not Before' }
    ];

    var present = DEFS.filter(function (c) { return payload[c.key] !== undefined; });

    if (present.length === 0) {
      specialClaims.classList.add('hidden');
      claimsDivider.classList.add('hidden');
      return;
    }

    specialClaims.classList.remove('hidden');
    claimsDivider.classList.remove('hidden');

    var html = '';
    present.forEach(function (c, i) {
      var key   = c.key;
      var label = c.label;
      var raw   = payload[key];
      var infoHtml = '';

      if (key === 'exp') {
        var expired = Date.now() > raw * 1000;
        var dStr = formatDate(raw);
        var rStr = relativeTime(raw);
        infoHtml = expired
          ? '<div style="color:#ef4444;font-weight:600;font-size:0.7rem;margin-top:2px;">Expired ' + escHtml(rStr) + '</div><div style="color:var(--fg3);font-size:0.68rem;">' + escHtml(dStr) + '</div>'
          : '<div style="color:var(--accent);font-weight:600;font-size:0.7rem;margin-top:2px;">Valid (' + escHtml(rStr) + ')</div><div style="color:var(--fg3);font-size:0.68rem;">' + escHtml(dStr) + '</div>';
      } else if (key === 'iat' || key === 'nbf') {
        infoHtml = '<div style="color:var(--fg3);font-size:0.68rem;margin-top:2px;">' + escHtml(formatDate(raw)) + '</div>';
      }

      var isLast = i === present.length - 1;
      html += '<div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;padding:7px 0;' + (isLast ? '' : 'border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);') + '">';
      html +=   '<span style="font-family:\'Fira Code\',monospace;font-size:0.71rem;color:var(--accent);min-width:34px;padding-top:2px;">' + escHtml(key) + '</span>';
      html +=   '<div style="flex:1;min-width:0;">';
      html +=     '<div style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--fg);word-break:break-all;font-family:\'Fira Code\',monospace;">' + escHtml(String(raw)) + '</div>';
      html +=     infoHtml;
      html +=   '</div>';
      html +=   '<span style="font-size:0.67rem;color:var(--fg3);white-space:nowrap;padding-top:2px;">' + escHtml(label) + '</span>';
      html += '</div>';
    });

    specialClaims.innerHTML = html;
  }

  // ── Copy buttons ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  document.querySelectorAll('[data-copy]').forEach(function (btn) {
    btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
      var target = btn.getAttribute('data-copy');
      var text =
        target === 'header'    ? headerOutput.textContent :
        target === 'payload'   ? payloadOutput.textContent :
        target === 'signature' ? signatureOutput.textContent : '';

      if (!text) return;

      function flash() {
        var orig   = btn.textContent;
        var origBg = btn.style.background || 'rgba(16,185,129,0.1)';
        btn.textContent    = 'Copied!';
        btn.style.background = 'rgba(16,185,129,0.22)';
        setTimeout(function () {
          btn.textContent    = orig;
          btn.style.background = origBg;
        }, 2000);
      }

      if (navigator.clipboard) {
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(flash).catch(fallback);
      } else { fallback(); }

      function fallback() {
        var ta = document.createElement('textarea');
        ta.value = text;
        ta.style.cssText = 'position:fixed;top:-9999px;left:-9999px;opacity:0;';
        document.body.appendChild(ta);
        ta.select();
        try { document.execCommand('copy'); } catch (e) {}
        document.body.removeChild(ta);
        flash();
      }
    });
  });

  // ── Sample button ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  var sampleBtn = document.getElementById('sampleBtn');
  if (sampleBtn) {
    sampleBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {
      jwtInput.value = SAMPLE_JWT;
      decode();
      jwtInput.focus();
    });
  }

  // ── Input events ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  if (jwtInput) {
    jwtInput.addEventListener('input', decode);
    jwtInput.addEventListener('paste', function () { setTimeout(decode, 0); });
  }

  // ── FAQ accordion ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-q').forEach(function (btn) {
    btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
      var item    = btn.closest('.faq-item');
      var content = item.querySelector('.faq-a');
      var chevron = item.querySelector('.faq-chevron');
      var isOpen  = !content.classList.contains('hidden');
      content.classList.toggle('hidden', isOpen);
      if (chevron) chevron.style.transform = isOpen ? '' : 'rotate(180deg)';
    });
  });

})();
</script>
